<br>
I just don't get people's problem with human vision. Are people really having that much trouble seeing things? When I'm on a CR, the only time it comes into play, if I go into a dark tunnel with no torches (most dungeons and tunnels have light sources in there) with lots of twists and turns is the only time I've had a problem. I think the only place this is a concern is the tunnel in everfrost to perma, which has a few stretches with no light at all and several turns.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, lightsource or UV or anything, just makes things a bit brighter. If you're having that big a problem, turn up the gamma some on your monitor or on the in-game gamma controls.<br>
